HEADWORD: Ignition
<hw>Ig*ni"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>ignition</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of igniting,
kindling, or setting on fire.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The state of being ignited or kindled.</def>
<rj><au>Sir T. Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ignitor</ent>⟦br⟧
